features: Compact design: The 7.1 inch wide compact structure provides strong spatial applicability and is suitable for various unused small spaces in your home, whether it is between the sofa and wall, or in the corner of the bathroom, between the toilet and the washbasin, etc.

Multi scenario use: This narrow end table can be used as a side table next to the sofa, or as a simple bedside table, magazine rack, reading table, corner table, snack table to store snacks, coffee, food, magazines, remote control, suitable for bathrooms, corridors, living rooms, bedrooms, offices, and more.

Adjustable V-shaped magazine rack: The skinny side table is designed with a V-shaped magazine rack for storing books, magazines, notebooks, etc. The angle of the "V" shape can also be changed according to your needs. Hollow out design allows you to quickly and intuitively find what you want.

Increase stability: The narrow side table is equipped with adjustable foot pads that can be adjusted according to the height of the ground to keep the side table level, increasing stability while preventing scratches on the indoor floor, etc.

Sturdy metal frame and mesh layer: The thickened metal frame and wood grain panel provide high load-bearing capacity for the small side table, while the combination of vintage panels and black painted metal perfectly blends modern industrial style into every corner of your interior.

Assembly is no longer a challenge: The narrow side tables for small spaces comes with detailed installation instructions inside the packaging, and each accessory has a corresponding number to help you quickly and easily assemble the Magazine table.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on January 28, 2024
reviews.reviewTitle: 2.0 out of 5 stars Arrived with broken magazine rack :(
reviews.reviewText: Arrived with a broken hinge for the magazine rack. It seemed to be well package, so I'm thinking it was broken before shipping.I had laid every piece out and made sure everything was there, BUT I didn't unfold the magazine rack! So I was half way through putting it together, grabbed the magazine rack to put it in, and noticed the broken hinge. VERY disappointed. I would not recommend buying this, but if you decide to chance it, make sure your magazine rack isn't broken BEFORE you start putting it together. :(I know it looks fine in the picture by the chair, but I put some clear tape on the broken corner of the magazine rack. It won't be strong enough to hold anything, but maybe I'll try hot gluing it in the future.Also, another side note, it isn't the most sturdy table. But, it is nice how small it is. Just be careful when you set your cup of tea down on it...
